	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Not nesdev related, but interesting (we're in the general forum).
<br />Do you think it's worth messing with 3D modeling in order to make better 2D graphics (such as in Donkey Kong Country) ?
<br />
<br />I could model simple geometric shapes with Blender, but honnestly I couldn't see how you could possibly model an human - even less how you could animate it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


