		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">For a 3d human model, recordings from motion capture sensors seem like the way to go.</div>
<br />
<br />A little off topic to your point but the problem with motion capture is the actors wearing the motion capture suites are too aware they are being motion captured and there movements always come out overly embellished and it dose not appear natural, so an many cases an animator setting the movements can look better.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
