	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I had considered getting into XNA game development a couple years ago. I quickly realized creating a lot of 3D models was going to be a problem. I looked around for free 3D models and there aren't very many good ones. It seems like most 3D model shops charge exorbitant prices for their stuff in many cases. It seems to me that is an obstacle for a lone developer who just wants to make a game. I wonder if there are many "open source" 3d model packs. Maybe Tepples will grant me my wish again. It wasn't really a wish though, since I'm now developing a nes game and do not need said free 3d models  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" />

		

